HEADWORD: Cerealin
<hw>Ce"re*a*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A nitrogenous substance closely resembling diastase, obtained from
bran, and possessing the power of converting starch into dextrin, sugar,
and lactic acid.</def> <rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerebel</ent>⟦br⟧
